 "summary": "The pullback API exposes only legitimate, minimal surface (all theorems, no helpers needing privacy), keeps all bodies unexposed, and provides a complete characteristic slice: forward preservation, surjective reflection, both iff forms, AddEquiv invariance, and the projection/product constructions. The class-based and explicit AddMonoidHom forms are not duplicates since a bare AddMonoidHom lacks a StarHomClass instance. No simp/grind annotations are warranted because the iff lemmas carry non-dischargeable hypotheses and the comp lemmas are not rewrite normal forms.",
